# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the user is responsible for mapping
#   their own environment. But for an app, ignore them.
.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used, it is sometimes ignored.
#   Uncomment if you want to ignore it.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#Poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#pdm.lock

